One of my goals for 2023 is to learn more about my body and overall physical health. I recently got a little head start by visiting @InovaHealth’s new Saville Cancer Screening and Prevention Center in Fairfax. Like many of us, I have seen the struggles and heartbreak that cancer causes and want to do my best to lower my risks. On my tour of @inovahealth I learned that 30-50% of all cancer cases are preventable with diet exercise and lifestyle choices. 

The incredible staff at Inova is there to help not only assess your risk of developing cancer, but to help provide you with a proactive plan to reduce that risk. During my visit, I was able to see the many tools Inova uses for prevention and early detection and even take a wellness, InBody Test. 

Join me in the new year and try one of Invova’s screenings as part of your regular healthcare routine. #InovaHealth #InovaSaville #InovaScharCancerInstitute #sponsored

2022. 

Truly the best year of my life (so far) & I mean that. 🥲🥹

First year living with @dmamb, creating a magical space together.  A @nytimes feature!! Experimented more with my personal style. Ran all over the Mediterranean with @aj_dc for a month, then a dream trip Alaska with @dmamb to see family and explore the massive state. These are run-on sentences but let’s keep going. 

I started running for the first time in my life and stuck with it. Something I’d never believe anyone if they told me. 

Visited @serenbe, LA, NYC, & WI as much as possible. 

Toasted to @juleslive_ & @officialtopben in the Catskills and @ellenjoyk & @dr_gaspar in Cape Cod. Upstaged the brides 😉 for @cherried_ & @yyyyyasha in DC. 

Ate as much lobster as I could in Maine with our crew. 

Visited Philly, ate delicious food, cherished my best friendship @eisayeff and hung out with @adl5107 & Daisy girl 🌼

Dozens of disco 🪩 ball installs around DC. 

Got fully addicted to TikTok, grew it a little, and made some friends IRL from it @pigmamiii @svnthevan 💋 

And above all, started my dream shop @libbyandmy with beautiful images from @mariahmirandaphoto & @aphraadkins.creative and surpassed amy goals for the first month in business. 

So much more than mentioned but, honestly it was just perfect. I can’t wait for 2023 but will always hold 2022 so near and dear to my heart. ❤️
Chosen family ❤️🦞🥂✨

An extremely fun year for outfits. 

I made a goal early last year to be more expressive with my clothing. 

Wear color, neutrals, thrifted & vintage pieces, designer sprinkled in, feel comfortable but also sexy, make thoughtful purchases, rent pieces, and occasionally splurge on some one of a kind looks. It was such a fun personal challenge and I have a lot of friends on tiktok to thank for the inspo, and even the haters for “not getting it” but whatever. 

Its made me happy and I’m excited to keep exploring more in 2023. More archival designer pieces, pattern mixing, taking better care of my shoes (and investing in nicer ones) more silk scarves and vintage pieces, and most importantly, repurposing old beloved pieces.☺️

You all know I’m a big fan of dry cleaning my clothes to keep them pristine and long-lasting and I’m so excited that @zipscleaners recently opened more locations! 
ZIPS started out as eight separate dry cleaners in the Baltimore-Washington, D.C. area. Since then, ZIPS has expanded to over 65 locations across the country. ZIPS’s goal is to provide high-quality dry cleaning at low prices while still giving the best service possible. 

They offer dry cleaning services, laundered and press items, Wash N Fold service, and you can even bring in some household items like comforters, which, reminder, is always a good idea to do! 

They even have a hanger recycling program and are committed to keeping hangers out of landfills and their bags are 100% recyclable. Check out your local ZIPS today! #321ZIPS #ZIPS #ad

HUGO SPRITZ RECIPE ft @svnthevan 
SAVE THIS for your next cocktail! 

My all time favorite cocktail I waste Italy has every day in Italy last summer. Incredibly easy to make and a great way to stay cool #hugospritz 

Ingredients: 
1/2 ounce @stgermaindrinks 
1 sprig mint
4 ounces prosecco, chilled
1 ounce soda water, chilled
Garnish: mint sprig and lemon or lime wheel 

Steps:
Add the St. Germain and mint sprig into a wine glass. Gently muddle and let sit for 3 minutes.

Add ice, the prosecco and the soda water and stir briefly and gently to combine.

Garnish with a mint sprig and a lemon wheel.

✨ Reflecting on History & Social Justice ✨

Step into a world of immersive wonder at the @NationalBuildingMuseum’s latest Summer Block Party installation exhibition - LOOK HERE! 🌟 This year’s jaw-dropping installation, designed by the talented architect Suchi Reddy of @ReddymadeDesign, invites you to explore the intersection of buildings and social justice.

Mirrors shaped like origami fortune tellers, towering nine-foot kaleidoscopes, and images of historic activist marches come together to create an unforgettable experience, allowing you to envision yourself as part of DC’s most significant moments.

Don’t miss this opportunity to be a part of history and see how buildings shape our society! Visit the Great Hall Thursdays - Mondays from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. until September 4th and make sure to check out their series of “Late Nights,” featuring music, food, and drink on July 27, August 10, and August 24 from 6:30 - 9:30pm.

Elevating my favorite snack with a twist on a classic favorite using @patagoniaprovisions’ Wild Sockeye Salmon! 🐟🥟 Let’s dive into the deliciousness together. 

✨Begin with velvety cream cheese, vibrant scallions, a touch of Worcestershire, and a drizzle of soy sauce or tamari for that irresistible umami.

✨Introduce the star of the show – the Wild Sockeye Salmon – and blend it all into a harmonious symphony of flavors.

✨Preheat your cooking oil in a pot, while you get those delicate wonton wrappers ready for action.

✨Seal the deal with a dab of water, securing the wrappers and arranging them lovingly on a baking sheet.

✨It’s sizzle time! Gently drop your salmon-loaded rangoons into the hot oil for that perfect golden crisp.

✨A quick pat-down to bid adieu to excess oil, and then it’s time to relish the warm, savory goodness!

Join me in this culinary escapade, and let’s celebrate the art of flavor with #PatagoniaProvisions. 🌊🍽️ #partner #tinnedfish

🧡 blessings from Kyoto

Went to the Bamboo Grove today and at the end of our walk, an older man on the side of the road was making bamboo dragonflies. As we handed him our money, he took our hand and placed the dragonfly on it and said “balance” 🎋 #kyoto

Our Kyoto shrine tour was made all the more special with Daisuke showing us around his home town in this beautiful Japanese version of the Rolls-Royce, The Century. 

We knew we wanted to maximize seeing as much of Kyoto in a short period of time + experience one of these classic and beautiful cars while we were here. Plus, after almost a week of walking in Tokyo our feet needed a break! 

Dai told us his name means great helper and this couldn’t have been more true. He was so incredibly warm and kind and made yesterday one of my favorite days so far. We prayed alongside him, ate mochi and had tea together. He told us that the pine tree, (matsu) is beloved in Japan for many reasons and one is that even when the needles fall off the tree, they fall in a pair of two, representing togetherness and connection. 

I was so touched by our morning with Dai and hope to see him when we return to Japan someday. 🌲

My friend @rondavidstudio sent me off to Japan 🇯🇵 with this amazing pleated top that gave drama & elegance all at once. The best part, amidst a closet of unpacked & very wrinkled clothing, it kept its shape and beautifully, making it the perfect piece for travel. ♥️ paired with some vintage @shopkaleidos trousers it’s one of my favorite fits of the trip!

social_posts.post_text:
Best bite of the trip so far. 

Ichimonjiya Wasuke ✨This family-owned shop has been serving toasted mochi for 1,022 years+, a tradition dating back to the year 1000 and is operated by the 25th generation of the same family. Wild. The building itself is older than the United States. 

What an honor to experience it while in Kyoto. #Ichiwa #kyoto

David and I have been saying prayers together more recently at home. We’re not religious per say, but just sending good thoughts to our family and reflecting on our gratitude, nightly has been a beautiful thing. We “freestyle” some nights, and say the bedtime prayer that I’ve said in my childhood on others. idk it feels weird to talk about praying on here but here we are! We prayed so much yesterday in Kyoto and watched families go to the shrines and temples together, we saw part of a wedding, lots of Grandmas, I was watery-eyed the whole day. Religion aside, prayer has really felt good to me lately and I’m just so grateful to be here doing it. #kyoto #YasakaKoshindo #yasakashrine

Kinosaki really turned our “pajamas during dinner” game up a notch. I loved them so much a bought a @nishimuraya.kinosaki yukata for home. 👘🥲 So special. 

#kinosakionsen #kinosaki #nishimurayahonkan #yukata

Another reason I cried in Japan. This meal. 

Mikawa Zezankyo (みかわ是山居) is owned by one of the best tempura chefs in Japan. Chef Saotome has a 60+ year experience in cooking tempura and has been living his life for creating the finest tempura dishes since he was about 15 years old. The restaurant received 1 Michelin star and it’s one of the highest scored restaurants on the Tabelog website. I knew it was going to be good but I wasn’t expecting a photo with Chef AND a signed menu. 🥲 what a dream. #tokyo #mikawazezankyo #tempuratokyo

The best ramen I’ve ever had and how we got into @ginza_hachigou. 🍜 

Firstly, a little background: Chef Yasufumi Matsumura's approach to ramen is something special. Instead of relying on traditional sauces, they create a unique soup using duck, free-range chicken, vegetables, and dry-cured ham, almost like preparing a consommé in French cuisine. The broth is both decadent yet CLEAN. it was like any ramen I’ve had. 

Now for getting in: no reservations, you must line up. We got there at 8am sharp to find out if 1. We could get a seat and 2. If so, for what time. We paid at the vending machine inside the door and got the 11:30am seating. There are 6 seats total.

We then killed some time in Ginza for the three hours we had. Went back to the fish market and window shopped. 

We came back around 11:15am and had some of the most heavenly ramen. Coincidentally, there was angelic chorale music gently playing which really added to the moment. Eat & slurp fast so the next seating can get in. The guy next to us seemed to be somewhat of a regular and no joke ate his in 2 minutes or less. Wild. 

Bring cash, show up early, and if you don’t get it the first time, try again the next. Worth it. I’ll be dreaming of this broth for years. 

Just be prepared for potentially long queues at the door, and don't forget that they only accept cash (yen). The intimate setting with seating for just 6 people adds to the charm of this place.

Experiencing the largest city in the world is so humbling. 

Like you’ve never seen so many people in one place all with separate agendas and needs for that day. 

At a concert or sporting event, you’re all there intentionally to group together. Tokyo on a Tuesday is just wild to see. Everyone going their own way. It’s like a movie or waves colliding. I can’t really describe it but thinking about this many different people’s individual lives is too much for me to comprehend. Do you ever get that feeling too? Heady thoughts as I return home. Either way, it was wild.

@ginza_bongen in the morning 🍵🧊

Hot tip: this is around the corner from @ginza_hachigou 🍜 so after you get your ticket from them, head over here to grab a matcha 🍵 and shop for jeans👖at @kapitalglobal in Ginza. #ginzatokyo #bongencoffee

We got engaged this weekend and exchanged promises and gifts to one another. With both our parents around for the weekend - it couldn’t have been more perfect. I love you with all my heart @dmamb 🤍

She’s an antique.🤍

My Toi et Moi ring is over 100 years old with the two diamonds representing “You and Me”. 

I don’t have many family heirlooms, so this really means so much to me. I hope that someday, inshallah, we will have two children and each can have a stone for their partners and families. I know it sounds like I’m getting ahead of myself but thinking about our future generations is always on my mind. I love my parents and loved my grandparents so much and think about them all the time. I love dreaming about my grandchildren some day having a piece of this ring and David’s tie tack as heirlooms and remembrance of David and I in 2023. 

Our engagement was filled with so many beautiful moments, I’m still not over it. And looking down at this beautiful ring is just surreal. #engagementring #toietmoi

I’ve talked about this before but when I was very little, I was bit in the face by a dog on Christmas Eve. And while I was too young to remember, I always kept my distance from dogs and never really saw myself being an owner of one. Now she’s here and she’s my little shadow. 

She loves when David comes home from work and laying close to the fireplace with me. I love her so much and I cant wait to see her grow.
